```

```
    public void received(Channel channel, Object message) throws RemotingException {
        ExecutorService executor = getPreferredExecutorService(message);

        if (message instanceof Request) {
            try {
                executor.execute(new ChannelEventRunnable(channel, handler, ChannelState.RECEIVED, message));
            } catch (Throwable t) {
                // FIXME: when the thread pool is full, SERVER_THREADPOOL_EXHAUSTED_ERROR cannot return properly,
                // therefore the consumer side has to wait until gets timeout. This is a temporary solution to prevent
                // this scenario from happening, but a better solution should be considered later.
                if (t instanceof RejectedExecutionException) {
                    sendFeedback(channel, (Request) message, t);
                }
                throw new ExecutionException(message, channel, getClass() + " error when process received event.", t);
            }
        } else if (executor instanceof ThreadlessExecutor) {
            executor.execute(new ChannelEventRunnable(channel, handler, ChannelState.RECEIVED, message));
        } else {
            handler.received(channel, message);
        }
    }
```
when the thread pool is full, SERVER_THREADPOOL_EXHAUSTED_ERROR cannot return properly, therefore the consumer side has to wait until gets timeout， 我们想问的是为什么不能正常返回？为什么不加sendFeedback(channel, (Request) message, t)代码，客户端一直要等到超时？

> @chickenlj are you sure? jdk only provide use SynchronousQueue, not LinkedBlockingQueue

In JDK     

```java
    public static ExecutorService newFixedThreadPool(int nThreads, ThreadFactory threadFactory) {
        return new ThreadPoolExecutor(nThreads, nThreads,
                                      0L, TimeUnit.MILLISECONDS,
                                      new LinkedBlockingQueue<Runnable>(),
                                      threadFactory);
    }

    public static ExecutorService newCachedThreadPool(ThreadFactory threadFactory) {
        return new ThreadPoolExecutor(0, Integer.MAX_VALUE,
                                      60L, TimeUnit.SECONDS,
                                      new SynchronousQueue<Runnable>(),
                                      threadFactory);
    }
```

CachedThreadPool is more like a extend for `newCachedThreadPool`, support customize queue.

@fengbaicanhe Very sorry to solve the problem you feedback so late.

This issue cannot reproduce on `master` branch you have mentioned 

```java
private void saveInExtensionClass(Map<String, Class<?>> extensionClasses, Class<?> clazz, String name, boolean overridden) {
	Class<?> c = extensionClasses.get(name);
	if (c == null || overridden) {
		extensionClasses.put(name, clazz);
	} else if (c != clazz) {
		String duplicateMsg = "Duplicate extension " + type.getName() + " name " + name + " on " + c.getName() + " and " + clazz.getName();
		logger.error(duplicateMsg);
		throw new IllegalStateException(duplicateMsg);
	}
}
```

From the `master` branch, we can see that there are two conditions that will not result in a Duplicate Exception

+ `c == null`: if it's the first time to load the class with the given name
+ `overridden == true`: it depends on `LoadingStrategy`

For all of default loading strategies, The values of `overridden`  are list as follows:

+ [DubboLoadingStrategy](https://github.com/apache/dubbo/blob/master/dubbo-common/src/main/java/org/apache/dubbo/common/extension/DubboLoadingStrategy.java#L33)'s `overridden` is `true`, which is used to resolve `META-INF/dubbo/com.limore.ExtensionConflict`
+ [ServicesLoadingStrategy](https://github.com/apache/dubbo/blob/master/dubbo-common/src/main/java/org/apache/dubbo/common/extension/ServicesLoadingStrategy.java#L33)'s `overridden` is `true`
+ [DubboInternalLoadingStrategy](https://github.com/apache/dubbo/blob/master/dubbo-common/src/main/java/org/apache/dubbo/common/extension/DubboInternalLoadingStrategy.java)'s `overridden` is `false`, which is used to resolve `META-INF/dubbo/internal/com.limore.ExtensionConflict`

We can see the implement class defined in `META-INF/dubbo/internal/com.limore.ExtensionConflict` can be overridden, so the situation you mentioned will never occur.



Also, I have check the [dubbo 2.6.6](https://github.com/apache/dubbo/releases/tag/dubbo-2.6.6), which is released on Feb 28, 2019 (The day after you asked the question)

```java
private void loadClass(Map<String, Class<?>> extensionClasses, java.net.URL resourceURL, Class<?> clazz, String name) throws NoSuchMethodException {
        ......
        if (clazz.isAnnotationPresent(Adaptive.class)) {
